      "content": "Stopping antibiotics early is a serious mistake because the remaining bacteria are often the most resistant, leading to a relapse that can be much harder to treat. Your immune system is not strong enough to clear a bacterial infection on its own once the medication is stopped, which is why completing the full course is non-negotiable for your long-term health. The \"unnecessary\" feeling you have is a common misconception, but the real cost of stopping early is a significantly higher risk of developing permanent antibiotic resistance.",
